description: Ireland's health minister warns there are concerns of a second wave with a rise in foreign travel.
title: Coronavirus: Ireland sees rise in percentage of cases coming from international travel
title_page: Coronavirus: Ireland sees rise in percentage of cases coming from international travel - BBC News
maintext: "In fairness to the airlines, it looks like they have taken an awful lot of steps so that they are complying with the EU regulations, but what the public health officials would say is, there is no zero risk," he added.
